@Marzipanherz, true, not all letters can directly translate into another language, another example that I struggle to come up with is Russian 'ц'. Yet other letters translate really well ( at least in the example of Rus-Eng): d,t,n,m, etc. 
I found one source, where I think it all came from: https://palaman.livejournal.com/260927.html
It was just an idea by one Russian author, so I don't know if there is any research on it, or how if this technique is used anywhere...

@AML Few loan words! 
Arabic loans words in Persian vocabulary approach 25 percent of a text in literature. According to another source, about 40% of everyday Persian literary vocabulary is of Arabic origin.
[Persian language Wikipedia. page](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language)
